citation: Proclamation under the Occupational Licensing (Automatic Mutual Recognition Consequential Amendments) Act 2022 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Occupational Licensing (Automatic Mutual Recognition Consequential Amendments) Act 2022

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Occupational Licensing (Automatic Mutual Recognition Consequential Amendments) Act 2022 , fix 14 December 2022 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, other than Parts 2, 3 and 7, commence.

13 December 2022

B.BAKER

Governor

By Her Excellency's Command,

ELISE ARCHER

Minister for Workplace Safety and Consumer Affairs

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 14 December 2022

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
